{"id": "ChIJLU-yFOTHwoARas1rwue29Zc", "rating": 4.4, "priceLevel": "PRICE_LEVEL_INEXPENSIVE", "userRatingCount": 474, "displayName": {"text": "Amboy Quality Meats & Delicious Burgers", "languageCode": "en"}, "editorialSummary": {"text": "Casual Filipino restaurant featuring a small selection of grilled meats, vegetables & bean dishes.", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJLU-yFOTHwoARas1rwue29Zc/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21sbE1GRjNXbGR4ZWxsUVMwbzFVbFpHY0VVd2VtYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "This is a hidden gem in Chinatown. Not a lot of seating for customers, but throughput is fast, so you’ll eventually get a table by the time your food is ready. Food portion is great and tasty. Chili cheese dog has just the right amount of heat and burger was delicious. A little disappointed with the tuna melt as the cheese was not melted and was still cold. Fries are done just right and perfect for sharing. All in all, a fun eating experience with decent pricing.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "This is a hidden gem in Chinatown. Not a lot of seating for customers, but throughput is fast, so you’ll eventually get a table by the time your food is ready. Food portion is great and tasty. Chili cheese dog has just the right amount of heat and burger was delicious. A little disappointed with the tuna melt as the cheese was not melted and was still cold. Fries are done just right and perfect for sharing. All in all, a fun eating experience with decent pricing.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Bessie Gessner", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102923134050620080217/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWi3qo6BYI9aYU2G4JqOPMiE6SKuC8jYm--m0taqLnu-DfIYZ0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-23T23:14:53.925018606Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21sbE1GRjNXbGR4ZWxsUVMwbzFVbFpHY0VVd2VtYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21sbE1GRjNXbGR4ZWxsUVMwbzFVbFpHY0VVd2VtYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c7e414b24f2d:0x97f5b6e7c26bcd6a"}, {"name": "places/ChIJLU-yFOTHwoARas1rwue29Zc/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xZNFJFRTNORFZMZFVGaVlWQnhNRUpXYlZkdFZWRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "rating": 2, "text": {"text": "Let down by the recommendation. If you're looking for where this is located, it's inside the old Asian Plaza building, more notably known by Howlin’ Rays, in between Alpine Street & Ord Street. The restaurant itself is very small and more quick-bite oriented than dine-in. Disappointed really is how this turned out, chili cheese fries, two different kinds of burgers. Chili cheese fries were simple yet effective; the chili was on the sweeter side and simple. The onions had a nice touch to the whole thing, although the price for such was on the higher end, \"$11.\" One burger was decent, \"$14,\" while the Amboy, \"$21,\" wasn't worth the price, especially since my burger was not fully cooked. Their excuse was it's served medium rare, but my patty is clearly raw and confirmed under temperature. Interestingly, the overall flavor was quite flat and very rare in a restaurant—under salted! Which can be a good thing depending on you as a person. The buns also weren't that great as a whole package. I did end up with the squirts the following day, sadly, repeatedly. In the end, no matter how fancy you try to make something, it's just a burger. This is why we end up going back to In-N-Out and just order it however you would like it, with the consistency, discipline, and willingness to make it right. Overall spent $55 on just myself definitely a luxury catered meal.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Let down by the recommendation. If you're looking for where this is located, it's inside the old Asian Plaza building, more notably known by Howlin’ Rays, in between Alpine Street & Ord Street. The restaurant itself is very small and more quick-bite oriented than dine-in. Disappointed really is how this turned out, chili cheese fries, two different kinds of burgers. Chili cheese fries were simple yet effective; the chili was on the sweeter side and simple. The onions had a nice touch to the whole thing, although the price for such was on the higher end, \"$11.\" One burger was decent, \"$14,\" while the Amboy, \"$21,\" wasn't worth the price, especially since my burger was not fully cooked. Their excuse was it's served medium rare, but my patty is clearly raw and confirmed under temperature. Interestingly, the overall flavor was quite flat and very rare in a restaurant—under salted! Which can be a good thing depending on you as a person. The buns also weren't that great as a whole package. I did end up with the squirts the following day, sadly, repeatedly. In the end, no matter how fancy you try to make something, it's just a burger. This is why we end up going back to In-N-Out and just order it however you would like it, with the consistency, discipline, and willingness to make it right. Overall spent $55 on just myself definitely a luxury catered meal.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Jesse Jones", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116682978303179060438/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUNELDBlqTfdpKmwZTfQ6hSymmzi63XJCsRPc8dudDd56F_T573Fw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"}, "publishTime": "2026-01-19T01:50:17.155819067Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xZNFJFRTNORFZMZFVGaVlWQnhNRUpXYlZkdFZWRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xZNFJFRTNORFZMZFVGaVlWQnhNRUpXYlZkdFZWRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c7e414b24f2d:0x97f5b6e7c26bcd6a"}, {"name": "places/ChIJLU-yFOTHwoARas1rwue29Zc/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2s1ZlprTk5RVGhNV25sRmRVTmFWVUpWYmkwd2NYYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "I stopped by Amboy Burgers after coming to Union Station on the Greyhound from San Diego. The place had a small line outside but it moved quickly. Since it was my first time, I ordered the classic Amboy burger with yellow peppers, and went to sit at a table outside.\n\nI was en route to LAX and realized my phone battery was quite low. I asked the clerk if I could charge my phone for a bit and he graciously plugged me in behind the counter. The burger itself was really good. It tasted like what I’d call a crossover of In-N-Out and a hole-in-the-wall smashburger spot. The meat was super flavorful, though, and the bun was quite good too.\n\nThe only downside is that it was like ~$18 after tax for a fairly small burger. But, I realize this is Los Angeles in 2026, so I let it slide and not interfere with my interpretation of the burger. Plus, the willingness to let me charge was really nice.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I stopped by Amboy Burgers after coming to Union Station on the Greyhound from San Diego. The place had a small line outside but it moved quickly. Since it was my first time, I ordered the classic Amboy burger with yellow peppers, and went to sit at a table outside.\n\nI was en route to LAX and realized my phone battery was quite low. I asked the clerk if I could charge my phone for a bit and he graciously plugged me in behind the counter. The burger itself was really good. It tasted like what I’d call a crossover of In-N-Out and a hole-in-the-wall smashburger spot. The meat was super flavorful, though, and the bun was quite good too.\n\nThe only downside is that it was like ~$18 after tax for a fairly small burger. But, I realize this is Los Angeles in 2026, so I let it slide and not interfere with my interpretation of the burger. Plus, the willingness to let me charge was really nice.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Christopher Gorrie", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100975914999435988271/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvB6Mm4QddVkwZiLVQiMCdaMm8YOBQt0ZNeUWTxTrGs8Pqv0JWdQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7"}, "publishTime": "2026-01-26T05:17:05.789063828Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2s1ZlprTk5RVGhNV25sRmRVTmFWVUpWYmkwd2NYYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2s1ZlprTk5RVGhNV25sRmRVTmFWVUpWYmkwd2NYYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c7e414b24f2d:0x97f5b6e7c26bcd6a"}, {"name": "places/ChIJLU-yFOTHwoARas1rwue29Zc/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xGUWNHNDVYMU4wVVdGRFZGSTFSRU16UTAxclZVRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "We had 2 Amboy burgers, the DH and slim thicc. Both were very good burgers. We enjoyed the slim thicc more because it’s more balanced than the DH which was very meat-forward.\nFries were very crispy and the portion was very generous.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "We had 2 Amboy burgers, the DH and slim thicc. Both were very good burgers. We enjoyed the slim thicc more because it’s more balanced than the DH which was very meat-forward.\nFries were very crispy and the portion was very generous.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Jungho Lee", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115756085644053969950/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJjjQ2Mbx7rA_P_ld_MprDQSYPYQxfDAdjHNk9osYLRzEMN9Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2025-12-17T07:03:29.841554635Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xGUWNHNDVYMU4wVVdGRFZGSTFSRU16UTAxclZVRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xGUWNHNDVYMU4wVVdGRFZGSTFSRU16UTAxclZVRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c7e414b24f2d:0x97f5b6e7c26bcd6a"}, {"name": "places/ChIJLU-yFOTHwoARas1rwue29Zc/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT200NVZXWlJiM1poTUhwRlVrUlNkbGRJUVVvMGNrRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 3, "text": {"text": "After succumbing to the hype, I finally decided to check this place out and overall, I really thought it was just meh. The meat was of good quality, that much was apparent, but it was very underseasoned. The chili cheese fries were just as \"meh\" and the cheese sauce they used has a bit of sweetness which was a little offputting. I really wanted to have a mind-blowing experience because of all of the word of mouth this place gets, but I left feeling underwhelmed.\n\nUpdate: Make sure you get the meat well done.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "After succumbing to the hype, I finally decided to check this place out and overall, I really thought it was just meh. The meat was of good quality, that much was apparent, but it was very underseasoned. The chili cheese fries were just as \"meh\" and the cheese sauce they used has a bit of sweetness which was a little offputting. I really wanted to have a mind-blowing experience because of all of the word of mouth this place gets, but I left feeling underwhelmed.\n\nUpdate: Make sure you get the meat well done.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Brandon B.", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111783810282488208731/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuD-QU-aaeDSfNH7xlxPIrxXUySvgc0tHndOP2ia9lgY7A0cNv=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-22T03:11:09.247209428Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT200NVZXWlJiM1poTUhwRlVrUlNkbGRJUVVvMGNrRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/da